OL,1,D]S737{kkkc5FYoung viewers prefer TV    
OL,2,D]S555{jjj25Fsubtitles, research        
OL,3,D]Suuu{rrzq5Fsuggests                   
OL,4,T#######################################
OL,5, Young people are almost four times more
OL,6, likely than older viewers to watch TV  
OL,7, shows with subtitles, despite having   
OL,8, fewer hearing problems, according to   
OL,9, research by a captioning charity.      
OL,11,FFour out of five viewers aged 18-25    
OL,12,Fsaid they use subtitles all or part of 
OL,13,Fthe time, Stagetext's figures said.    
OL,15,FLess than a quarter of those aged      
OL,16,Fbetween 56 and 75 said they do so.     
OL,18,FBut people in that age bracket were    
OL,19,Falmost twice as likely to say they are 
OL,20,Fdeaf or hard of hearing.               
